ated population of 206 million according to extrapolation of the latest UN data, Nigeria has so far carried out a total of 151,121 tests, equivalent to 733 tests/million population. South Africa, with a population of 59,3 million has carried out 1.88 million tests equivalent to 30,854 tets/million population, while Ghana with a population of 31 million has done 310,159 tests equivalent to 9,980 tests/million population. While Nigeria recorded 139 COVID-19 cases/r million population and discharged a total of 11,665 persons after recovery, South Africa and Ghana have discharged 93,315 and 14,870 persons respectively. In terms of cases per million population, South Africa recorded 3,317 and Ghana, 646. With three deaths per million population, Nigeria has fewer deaths than South Africa and Ghana which recorded 54 and 4 respectively. Nigeria has a higher case fatality rate, CFR.of 0.2 per cent than the two other countries. Vanguard By Rasheed Sobowale The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) in its latest report on the coronavirus pandemic in Nigeria has confirmed 7,526 cases as at May 23rd. Nigeria, the most populous country in Africa has conducted about 43,000 tests for the virus. Of the total confirmed cases, NCDC noted… May 24, 2020 In "Coronavirus Updates" By Rasheed Sobowale Nigeria which recorded its first case of the coronavirus disease on February 27 has so far reported that 197 persons have recovered from the virus. The most populous nation in Western Africa on April 22 reported a total of 873 confirmed COVID-19 cases with 28 deaths so… April 23, 2020 In "Coronavirus Updates" The number of novel coronavirus (COVID-19) cases recorded worldwide surpassed four million on Saturday, according to an AFP tally based on official sources. There are now at least 4,001,437 cases of coronavirus around the world, with 277,127 deaths. The United States has been the hardest-hit country, with 1,305,544 cases and… May 10, 2020 In "Coronavirus Updates"